{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775854340311,"sessionID":"ses_286d7bf5effezn8f6G9VP0lIdu","part":{"id":"prt_d79284b97001fGiU9u0uzLgRoC","messageID":"msg_d79284197001Nu047o48GnrNQN","sessionID":"ses_286d7bf5effezn8f6G9VP0lIdu","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_06d600cfe40547dfb80f32d5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project at /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall project structure (directories, key files)\n2. The cmd/cli module - what exists there, how CLI commands are structured\n3. Any existing tasks.md files or similar checklists to understand the format\n4. Any existing \"publish\" related code or commands\n5. How other CLI commands are implemented (look at cmd/cli for patterns)\n6. Any configuration files, package.json, setup.py, pyproject.toml etc.\n7. Testing patterns - how tests are organized\n8. Any AR (Acceptance Requirements) or ST (Stage) documentation\n\nSearch broadly - look at root level files, cmd/ directory, cli/ directory, tests/, docs/, etc.\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of:\n- Project structure overview\n- CLI command patterns (how commands are defined, registered, tested)\n- Any existing tasks.md format\n- What \"publish\" might mean in this context (publishing packages? publishing agents? publishing configurations?)\n- Key files I should reference when writing the tasks.md","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_286d7972bffe5OOUDpykdZ7nr6 (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a thorough understanding of the entire project. Here is the comprehensive summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Project Summary: AgentCube\n\n### 1. Project Structure Overview\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/\n├── go.mod                          # Go module: github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube (Go 1.25)\n├── project.md                      # Project context document\n├── proposal.md                     # AR-019 proposal (4 Go binaries)\n├── design.md                       # AR-020 design (CLI pack command)\n├── delta-spec.md                   # AR-016 delta spec (PicoD file management)\n├── test_spec.md                    # Test specification\n├── .sdd_prompt.md                  # SDD prompt with full CLI spec/design\n│\n├── cmd/                            # Go binary entry points\n│   ├── agentd/                     # K8s Controller - sandbox idle cleanup (EXISTING)\n│   ├── picod/                      # Sandbox Daemon - code execution in pods (EXISTING)\n│   ├── workloadmanager/            # Workload Manager API server (NEW, AR-019)\n│   ├── router/                     # Session-aware HTTP router (NEW, AR-019)\n│   └── cli/                        # *** PYTHON CLI *** (not Go)\n│       ├── pyproject.toml          # Python package config (agentcube 0.1.0, Python >=3.10)\n│       ├── agentcube/\n│       │   ├── __init__.py         # __version__, exports app, PackRuntime, BuildRuntime\n│       │   ├── cli/\n│       │   │   └── main.py         # Typer app: pack(), build() commands implemented\n│       │   ├── models/\n│       │   │   └── pack_models.py  # MetadataOptions dataclass\n│       │   ├── runtime/\n│       │   │   ├── __init__.py\n│       │   │   ├── pack_runtime.py # PackRuntime - FULLY IMPLEMENTED\n│       │   │   └── build_runtime.py# BuildRuntime - FULLY IMPLEMENTED\n│       │   ├── services/\n│       │   │   ├── __init__.py\n│       │   │   ├── metadata_service.py  # AgentMetadata (Pydantic), MetadataService - IMPLEMENTED\n│       │   │   └── docker_service.py    # DockerService (check, build) - IMPLEMENTED\n│       │   └── operations/\n│       │       └── __init__.py     # Placeholder\n│       ├── tests/\n│       │   ├── cli/\n│       │   │   └── test_build_command.py\n│       │   ├── runtime/            # 11 test files for pack/build runtime\n│       │   ├── services/           # 3 test files for docker/metadata\n│       │   ├── models/             # (exists, referenced in tasks.md)\n│       │   └── integration/        # (exists, referenced in tasks.md)\n│       └── examples/\n│           ├── hello-agent/\n│           ├── math-agent/\n│           └── java-agent/\n│\n├── pkg/                            # Go packages\n│   ├── apis/                       # CRD type definitions (runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1)\n│   ├── agentd/\n│   ├── picod/\n│   ├── router/\n│   ├── store/\n│   ├── workloadmanager/\n│   └── common/\n│\n├── client-go/                      # Generated K8s typed client\n├── changes/                        # AR-001 through AR-022 (Acceptance Requirements)\n│   └── AR-NNN/\n│       ├── proposal.md\n│       ├── design.md\n│       ├── delta-spec.md\n│       └── tasks.md\n│\n├── cli-toolkit/\n│   ├── design.md                   # Full CLI design doc\n│   └── spec.md                     # Full CLI spec (Gherkin-style)\n│\n├── python-sdk/                     # Separate Python SDK\n├── deployment/                     # Deployment docs\n├── ci-cd/                          # CI/CD design/spec\n├── sandbox-orchestration/\n├── session-routing/\n├── session-store/\n├── code-execution/\n├── idle-cleanup/\n├── integrations/\n└── testing/\n```\n\n### 2. CLI Command Patterns\n\nThe Python CLI uses **Typer** (not Cobra/Go). Key patterns:\n\n**Command Registration** (`cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`):\n```python\napp = typer.Typer(\n    name=\"agentcube\",\n    help=\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\",\n    no_args_is_help=True,\n    rich_markup_mode=\"rich\",\n    add_completion=False,\n)\n\n@app.callback()\ndef main(version: Optional[bool] = typer.Option(...), verbose: bool = ...) -> None: ...\n\n@app.command()\ndef pack(workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", ...), ...) -> None:\n    with Progress(SpinnerColumn(), TextColumn(...), transient=True) as progress:\n        task = progress.add_task(\"Packaging agent...\", total=None)\n        try:\n            runtime = PackRuntime(verbose=verbose)\n            result = runtime.pack(workspace_path, **options)\n            # Rich success output\n        except Exception as e:\n            _handle_error(e, \"packaging agent\", verbose)\n```\n\n**Runtime Class Pattern** (e.g., `PackRuntime`, `BuildRuntime`):\n- `__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)` -- stores `self.verbose`, creates `MetadataService`\n- `public_method(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]` -- main entry\n- `_private_method(self, ...)` -- internal steps (validation, metadata, generation, etc.)\n\n**Error Handling** (consistent across all commands):\n```python\ndef _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n    console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n    if verbose:\n        console.print_exception()\n    raise typer.Exit(1)\n```\n\n**Console script entry**: `kubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"` (in pyproject.toml)\n\n### 3. tasks.md Format\n\nEvery `changes/AR-NNN/tasks.md` follows this structure:\n\n```markdown\n# AR-NNN — <Title> — Tasks\n\n> **Module:** cmd/cli\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-NNN/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-NNN/design.md`, ...\n\n## T1. <Task Title>\n\n- [ ] 1.1 <subtask description>\n- [ ] 1.2 <subtask description>\n...\n\n**Verification:** <specific command to verify>\n\n---\n\n## T2. <Task Title>\n...\n\n---\n\n## Task Dependencies\n\n```\n<ASCII dependency graph>\n```\n\n**Parallel execution:**\n- <bulleted list of parallelization notes>\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| # | Criterion | Command |\n|---|-----------|---------|\n| AC1 | ... | `kubectl-agentcube ...` |\n```\n\nKey characteristics:\n- Tasks are numbered T1, T2, ... with subtasks 1.1, 1.2, ...\n- Each task ends with a **Verification:** line specifying the exact test command\n- Task dependency graph in ASCII art\n- Parallel execution notes\n- Acceptance Criteria table at the end\n- AR-022/tasks.md is currently a **stub** (placeholder with \"Task 1/2/3\")\n\n### 4. What \"publish\" Means\n\n**\"Publish\" = deploying a packaged + built AI agent to Kubernetes.** It is the 3rd step in the lifecycle pipeline:\n\n```\npack → build → publish → invoke\n```\n\nSpecifically, the `publish` command:\n1. **Prepares the container image** -- either pushes a local Docker image to a registry (`build_mode=local`) or uses an existing cloud image URL (`build_mode=cloud`)\n2. **Deploys to Kubernetes** via one of two providers:\n   - **`agentcube`** (default): Creates/patches an `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource at `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/agentruntimes`\n   - **`k8s`**: Creates a standard `Deployment` + `NodePort Service`\n3. **Waits for deployment readiness** (120s timeout for k8s provider)\n4. **Updates `agent_metadata.yaml`** with deployment info (`agent_id`, `agent_endpoint`, `k8s_deployment`)\n\nIt is NOT about publishing Python packages to PyPI or Go modules. It is about **publishing/deploying AI agent workloads to Kubernetes**.\n\n### 5. Existing \"publish\" Related Code\n\n**AR-022** is the Acceptance Requirement for the publish command:\n- `changes/AR-022/proposal.md` -- Full proposal (583 lines)\n- `changes/AR-022/design.md` -- Full design (529 lines)\n- `changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md` -- Delta spec (324 lines)\n- `changes/AR-022/tasks.md` -- **STUB** (only 17 lines, placeholder tasks)\n\n**Files that need to be created/modified for publish:**\n| Action | File |\n|--------|------|\n| Modify | `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py` | Add `publish()` Typer command |\n| Create | `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` | `PublishRuntime` class |\n| Create | `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | `AgentCubeProvider` class |\n| Create | `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | `KubernetesProvider` class |\n| Modify | `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Add `push_image`, `_docker_login_sdk`, `_tag_image_sdk` |\n| Create | `cmd/cli/tests/cli/test_publish.py` | CLI publish command tests |\n| Create | `cmd/cli/tests/runtime/test_publish_runtime.py` | PublishRuntime unit tests |\n| Create | `cmd/cli/tests/services/test_agentcube_provider.py` | AgentCubeProvider tests |\n| Create | `cmd/cli/tests/services/test_k8s_provider.py` | KubernetesProvider tests |\n\n### 6. Testing Patterns\n\n**Test organization** mirrors source structure:\n```\ncmd/cli/tests/\n├── cli/test_build_command.py       # CLI command tests using typer.testing.CliRunner\n├── runtime/\n│   ├── test_build_runtime.py       # BuildRuntime orchestration tests\n│   ├── test_build_runtime_cloud.py\n│   ├── test_build_runtime_local.py\n│   ├── test_build_runtime_metadata.py\n│   ├── test_build_runtime_prerequisites.py\n│   ├── test_build_runtime_version.py\n│   ├── test_pack_runtime_*.py      # PackRuntime tests (by feature area)\n│   └── ...\n├── services/\n│   ├── test_docker_service.py\n│   ├── test_metadata_model.py      # AgentMetadata Pydantic validation tests\n│   └── test_metadata_service.py    # MetadataService load/save tests\n├── models/\n└── integration/\n```\n\n**Test patterns:**\n- Use `pytest` with `tmp_path` fixture for isolated workspaces\n- Use `unittest.mock.patch` for Docker/K8s client mocking\n- Use `typer.testing.CliRunner` for CLI command testing\n- Class-per-scenario naming: `TestBuildRuntimeLocalBuildSuccess`, `TestBuildCommandErrorNoVerbose`\n- Fixtures for common setup: `packed_workspace`, `runtime`, `base_metadata`\n- Quality gates: coverage >= 80%, T/C ratio > 0.4, ruff clean, mypy clean\n\n### 7. Key Files to Reference When Writing tasks.md for AR-022\n\n1. **`changes/AR-021/tasks.md`** (316 lines) -- Best template for a Python CLI command tasks.md. Same module (`cmd/cli`), same language (Python), similar complexity. Shows the exact format for T1-T10 pattern with DockerService, Runtime class, CLI command, E2E tests, and quality gates.\n\n2. **`changes/AR-020/tasks.md`** (606 lines) -- Another excellent reference for the `pack` command. Very detailed with 20 tasks.\n\n3. **`changes/AR-022/proposal.md`** -- Defines the scope, architecture, and acceptance criteria for publish.\n\n4. **`changes/AR-022/design.md`** -- Contains the full class signatures, data flow, test matrix, and mock strategies.\n\n5. **`changes/AR-022/delta-spec.md`** -- Contains all the Given/When/Then scenarios that must be covered.\n\n6. **`cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`** -- Current state of the CLI (has `pack` and `build`, needs `publish`).\n\n7. **`cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py`** -- Pattern to follow for `PublishRuntime`.\n\n8. **`cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`** -- Needs `push_image` method added.\n\n9. **`cli-toolkit/spec.md`** -- Contains the publish command spec requirements.\n\n10. **`cmd/cli/tests/cli/test_build_command.py`** -- Pattern for CLI command tests.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_286d7972bffe5OOUDpykdZ7nr6","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775854184657,"end":1775854340308}}}}
