{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775854352602,"sessionID":"ses_286d7bf5effezn8f6G9VP0lIdu","part":{"id":"prt_d792af450001xIlLRUxrcn5tnS","messageID":"msg_d792ae369001LYI7xn1mjDWpxz","sessionID":"ses_286d7bf5effezn8f6G9VP0lIdu","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_27ddbd1ef6674f55b137a019","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-022/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-022/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 — Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: The `publish` command deploys a packaged and built agent to a target Kubernetes cluster. It supports two providers:\n6: - **`agentcube`** (default): Deploys an AgentRuntime Custom Resource (CR) to `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n7: - **`k8s`**: Deploys standard Kubernetes Deployment + NodePort Service\n8: \n9: The command handles image preparation (local Docker push or cloud image URL), provider-specific deployment, metadata updates, and readiness verification. It is the third step in the agent lifecycle pipeline: `pack → build → publish → invoke`.\n10: \n11: ## Architecture\n12: \n13: ### 2.1 Data Flow\n14: \n15: ```\n16: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n17: │                          CLI (Typer)                                  │\n18: │   kubectl-agentcube publish -f <workspace> [--provider agentcube]    │\n19: └────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n20:                          │ options dict\n21:                          ▼\n22: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n23: │                       PublishRuntime                                  │\n24: │  ┌──────────────────┬──────────────────┬──────────────────────────┐  │\n25: │  │ _prepare_image_  │ _publish_cr_to_  │ _publish_k8s             │  │\n26: │  │ for_publishing   │ k8s              │                          │  │\n27: │  └────────┬─────────┴────────┬─────────┴────────────┬─────────────┘  │\n28: │           │                  │                      │                 │\n29: │           ▼                  ▼                      ▼                 │\n30: │  ┌────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────┐   │\n31: │  │ _prepare_local │  │ AgentCubeProvider│  │ KubernetesProvider │   │\n32: │  │ _image         │  │ .deploy_agent_   │  │ .deploy_agent()    │   │\n33: │  │ _prepare_cloud │  │ runtime()        │  │ .wait_for_deploy   │   │\n34: │  │ _image         │  │                  │  │ ment_ready()       │   │\n35: │  └────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └────────────────────┘   │\n36: │                                                                      │\n37: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n38: │  │ _update_publish_metadata() → agent_metadata.yaml               │  │\n39: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n40: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n41:                          │\n42:                          ▼\n43: ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n44: │                    Rich Output                                        │\n45: │  \"✓ Agent published successfully\"                                    │\n46: │    Agent: <name>  Provider: <provider>  Endpoint: <url>              │\n47: └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n48: ```\n49: \n50: ### 2.2 Package Layout (publish-relevant modules)\n51: \n52: ```\n53: cmd/cli/\n54: ├── pyproject.toml                     — Dependencies, console script entry\n55: ├── agentcube/\n56: │   ├── __init__.py                    — __version__, PublishRuntime export\n57: │   ├── cli/\n58: │   │   ├── __init__.py                — Subpackage marker\n59: │   │   └── main.py                    — Typer app, publish() command, _handle_error\n60: │   ├── models/\n61: │   │   └── pack_models.py             — MetadataOptions dataclass\n62: │   ├── runtime/\n63: │   │   ├── __init__.py                — Re-exports PublishRuntime\n64: │   │   └── publish_runtime.py         — PublishRuntime class\n65: │   └── services/\n66: │       ├── __init__.py                — Services package docstring\n67: │       ├── metadata_service.py         — AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n68: │       ├── docker_service.py           — DockerService (image push)\n69: │       ├── k8s_provider.py             — KubernetesProvider (Deployment + Service)\n70: │       └── agentcube_provider.py       — AgentCubeProvider (AgentRuntime CR)\n71: └── examples/\n72:     ├── hello-agent/main.py            — Example Python agent\n73:     └── math-agent/main.py             — Example Python agent\n74: ```\n75: \n76: ### 2.3 Dependencies\n77: \n78: | Module | Purpose |\n79: |--------|---------|\n80: | `typer[all]>=0.9.0` | CLI framework, Rich markup |\n81: | `pydantic>=2.0.0` | AgentMetadata validation |\n82: | `pyyaml>=6.0` | YAML load/dump for agent_metadata.yaml |\n83: | `docker>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for image push (local mode) |\n84: | `kubernetes>=28.0.0` | K8s client library (optional, for K8s provider) |\n85: | `rich>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner, colored output, tables |\n86: | `httpx>=0.24.0` | HTTP client (indirect, used by providers) |\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## Component Design\n91: \n92: ### 3.1 PublishRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`)\n93: \n94: ```python\n95: class PublishRuntime:\n96:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n97:     def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n98:     def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n99:     def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n100:     def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n101:     def _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n102:     def _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str: ...\n103:     def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None: ...\n104: ```\n105: \n106: ### 3.2 CLI Command Signature\n107: \n108: ```\n109: kubectl-agentcube publish [OPTIONS]\n110: ```\n111: \n112: | Option | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n113: |--------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n114: | `--workspace` | `-f` | `str` | `\".\"` | Path to the agent workspace directory |\n115: | `--version` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version string (e.g., v1.0.0) |\n116: | `--image-url` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Image repository URL (required in local build mode) |\n117: | `--image-username` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Username for image repository |\n118: | `--image-password` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Password for image repository |\n119: | `--description` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent description |\n120: | `--region` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n121: | `--cloud-provider` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Cloud provider name (e.g., huawei) |\n122: | `--provider` | — | `str` | `\"agentcube\"` | Target provider: `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) or `k8s` (Deployment/Service) |\n123: | `--node-port` | — | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Specific NodePort (30000-32767) for K8s deployment |\n124: | `--replicas` | — | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Number of replicas for K8s deployment (default: 1) |\n125: | `--namespace` | — | `Optional[str]` | `None` | The namespace for the deployment |\n126: | `--verbose` | — | `bool` | `False` | Enable detailed logging |\n127: \n128: ### 3.3 Sentinel Errors\n129: \n130: ```python\n131: # PublishRuntime\n132: ValueError(\"Workspace directory does not exist: {path}\")\n133: ValueError(\"Image URL is required for local build mode\")\n134: ValueError(\"router_url and workload_manager_url are required in agent_metadata.yaml for AgentCube provider\")\n135: ValueError(\"NodePort must be between 30000 and 32767\")\n136: RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n137: RuntimeError(\"Deployment {name} did not become ready within {timeout}s\")\n138: ```\n139: \n140: ---\n141: \n142: ## Data Flow\n143: \n144: ### 4.1 publish() Main Orchestration\n145: \n146: ```python\n147: def publish(self, workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n148:     # 1. Validate workspace path\n149:     if not workspace_path.exists():\n150:         raise ValueError(f\"Workspace directory does not exist: {workspace_path}\")\n151:     if not workspace_path.is_dir():\n152:         raise ValueError(f\"Workspace path is not a directory: {workspace_path}\")\n153: \n154:     # 2. Load metadata\n155:     service = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose)\n156:     metadata = service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n157: \n158:     # 3. Apply CLI option overrides\n159:     for key in [\"version\", \"description\", \"region\"]:\n160:         value = options.get(key)\n161:         if value is not None:\n162:             setattr(metadata, key, value)\n163: \n164:     # 4. Validate node_port range if provided\n165:     node_port = options.get(\"node_port\")\n166:     if node_port is not None and not (30000 <= node_port <= 32767):\n167:         raise ValueError(\"NodePort must be between 30000 and 32767\")\n168: \n169:     # 5. Prepare image for publishing\n170:     image_url = self._prepare_image_for_publishing(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n171: \n172:     # 6. Route to provider-specific publish\n173:     if self.provider == \"agentcube\":\n174:         result = self._publish_cr_to_k8s(workspace_path, metadata, image_url=image_url, **options)\n175:     elif self.provider == \"k8s\":\n176:         result = self._publish_k8s(workspace_path, metadata, image_url=image_url, **options)\n177:     else:\n178:         raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported provider: {self.provider}\")\n179: \n180:     # 7. Update metadata with deployment info\n181:     self._update_publish_metadata(workspace_path, result)\n182: \n183:     return result\n184: ```\n185: \n186: ### 4.2 Image Preparation Flow\n187: \n188: ```\n189: _prepare_image_for_publishing()\n190:          │\n191:          ├── metadata.build_mode == \"local\"\n192:          │        │\n193:          │        ├── image_url from CLI required\n194:          │        │\n195:          │        └── _prepare_local_image()\n196:          │                 │\n197:          │                 ├── DockerService.check_docker_available()\n198:          │                 ├── DockerService._docker_login_sdk() (if credentials)\n199:          │                 └── DockerService.push_image()\n200:          │\n201:          └── metadata.build_mode == \"cloud\"\n202:                   │\n203:                   └── _prepare_cloud_image()\n204:                            │\n205:                            └── Resolve cloud image URL from metadata/options\n206: ```\n207: \n208: ### 4.3 _prepare_image_for_publishing\n209: \n210: ```python\n211: def _prepare_image_for_publishing(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n212:     if metadata.build_mode == \"local\":\n213:         return self._prepare_local_image(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n214:     elif metadata.build_mode == \"cloud\":\n215:         return self._prepare_cloud_image(workspace_path, metadata, options)\n216:     else:\n217:         raise ValueError(f\"Unsupported build mode: {metadata.build_mode}\")\n218: ```\n219: \n220: ### 4.4 _prepare_local_image\n221: \n222: ```python\n223: def _prepare_local_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n224:     docker_service = DockerService(verbose=self.verbose)\n225: \n226:     if not docker_service.check_docker_available():\n227:         raise RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")\n228: \n229:     image_url = options.get(\"image_url\")\n230:     if not image_url:\n231:         raise ValueError(\"Image URL is required for local build mode\")\n232: \n233:     # Build image tag\n234:     version = metadata.version or \"latest\"\n235:     image_tag = f\"{image_url}:{version}\"\n236: \n237:     # Login if credentials provided\n238:     username = options.get(\"image_username\") or metadata.registry_username\n239:     password = options.get(\"image_password\") or metadata.registry_password\n240:     registry_url = options.get(\"registry_url\") or metadata.registry_url\n241: \n242:     if username and password:\n243:         docker_service._docker_login_sdk(registry_url, username, password)\n244: \n245:     # Push image\n246:     result = docker_service.push_image(image_tag, registry_url, username, password)\n247:     return result.get(\"pushed_image\", image_tag)\n248: ```\n249: \n250: ### 4.5 _prepare_cloud_image\n251: \n252: ```python\n253: def _prepare_cloud_image(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, options: Dict[str, Any]) -> str:\n254:     # Cloud build mode: image already built in cloud, resolve URL\n255:     image_url = options.get(\"image_url\")\n256:     if image_url:\n257:         return image_url\n258: \n259:     if metadata.image and metadata.image.get(\"url\"):\n260:         return metadata.image[\"url\"]\n261: \n262:     raise ValueError(\"Image URL is required for cloud build mode\")\n263: ```\n264: \n265: ### 4.6 AgentCube Provider Flow (_publish_cr_to_k8s)\n266: \n267: ```python\n268: def _publish_cr_to_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n269:     # Validate prerequisites\n270:     if not metadata.router_url:\n271:         raise ValueError(\"router_url and workload_manager_url are required in agent_metadata.yaml for AgentCube provider\")\n272:     if not metadata.workload_manager_url:\n273:         raise ValueError(\"router_url and workload_manager_url are required in agent_metadata.yaml for AgentCube provider\")\n274: \n275:     # Initialize provider\n276:     namespace = options.get(\"namespace\") or \"default\"\n277:     provider = AgentCubeProvider(namespace=namespace, verbose=self.verbose)\n278: \n279:     # Deploy AgentRuntime CR\n280:     result = provider.deploy_agent_runtime(\n281:         agent_name=metadata.agent_name,\n282:         image_url=options.get(\"image_url\", \"\"),\n283:         port=metadata.port,\n284:         entrypoint=metadata.entrypoint,\n285:         env_vars={},\n286:         workload_manager_url=metadata.workload_manager_url,\n287:         router_url=metadata.router_url,\n288:         readiness_probe_path=metadata.readiness_probe_path,\n289:         readiness_probe_port=metadata.readiness_probe_port,\n290:     )\n291: \n292:     # Wait for CR readiness (poll status)\n293:     # ... polling logic ...\n294: \n295:     return {\n296:         \"agent_id\": result.get(\"name\"),\n297:         \"agent_endpoint\": result.get(\"endpoint\"),\n298:         \"namespace\": namespace,\n299:         \"k8s_deployment\": {\n300:             \"type\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n301:             \"namespace\": namespace,\n302:             \"cr_name\": result.get(\"name\"),\n303:         },\n304:     }\n305: ```\n306: \n307: ### 4.7 Kubernetes Provider Flow (_publish_k8s)\n308: \n309: ```python\n310: def _publish_k8s(self, workspace_path: Path, metadata, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n311:     namespace = options.get(\"namespace\") or \"default\"\n312:     replicas = options.get(\"replicas\") or 1\n313:     node_port = options.get(\"node_port\")\n314: \n315:     provider = KubernetesProvider(namespace=namespace, verbose=self.verbose)\n316: \n317:     # Deploy Deployment + Service\n318:     result = provider.deploy_agent(\n319:         agent_name=metadata.agent_name,\n320:         image_url=options.get(\"image_url\", \"\"),\n321:         port=metadata.port,\n322:         entrypoint=metadata.entrypoint,\n323:         replicas=replicas,\n324:         node_port=node_port,\n325:         env_vars={},\n326:     )\n327: \n328:     # Wait for deployment readiness\n329:     try:\n330:         provider.wait_for_deployment_ready(result[\"deployment_name\"], timeout=120)\n331:     except TimeoutError:\n332:         raise RuntimeError(f\"Deployment {result['deployment_name']} did not become ready within 120s\")\n333: \n334:     return {\n335:         \"deployment_name\": result[\"deployment_name\"],\n336:         \"service_name\": result[\"service_name\"],\n337:         \"service_url\": result[\"service_url\"],\n338:         \"namespace\": namespace,\n339:         \"replicas\": replicas,\n340:         \"node_port\": result.get(\"node_port\"),\n341:         \"k8s_deployment\": {\n342:             \"type\": \"Deployment\",\n343:             \"namespace\": namespace,\n344:             \"deployment_name\": result[\"deployment_name\"],\n345:             \"service_url\": result[\"service_url\"],\n346:         },\n347:     }\n348: ```\n349: \n350: ### 4.8 _update_publish_metadata\n351: \n352: ```python\n353: def _update_publish_metadata(self, workspace_path: Path, agent_info: Dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n354:     service = MetadataService(verbose=self.verbose)\n355:     updates = {\n356:         \"agent_id\": agent_info.get(\"agent_id\"),\n357:         \"agent_endpoint\": agent_info.get(\"agent_endpoint\") or agent_info.get(\"service_url\"),\n358:         \"k8s_deployment\": agent_info.get(\"k8s_deployment\"),\n359:     }\n360:     service.update_metadata(workspace_path, updates)\n361: ```\n362: \n363: ---\n364: \n365: ## Error Handling\n366: \n367: ### 5.1 Error Handling Strategy\n368: \n369: | Error Type | Handling | Exit Code |\n370: |------------|----------|-----------|\n371: | Workspace validation failure | `_handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)` | 1 |\n372: | Docker unavailable (local mode) | `_handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)` | 1 |\n373: | Missing image URL | `_handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)` | 1 |\n374: | Missing router_url/workload_manager_url (agentcube) | `_handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)` | 1 |\n375: | Invalid node_port range | `_handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)` | 1 |\n376: | Deployment readiness timeout | `_handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)` | 1 |\n377: | K8s client initialization failure | `_handle_error(e, \"publish\", verbose)` | 1 |\n378: \n379: ### 5.2 CLI Error Handler\n380: \n381: ```python\n382: def _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n383:     console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n384:     if verbose:\n385:         console.print_exception()\n386:     raise typer.Exit(1)\n387: ```\n388: \n389: ### 5.3 Verbose vs Global Verbose\n390: \n391: The subcommand's local `--verbose` flag is passed to `_handle_error`, ensuring traceback is printed even if global `-v` was not passed on the root callback.\n392: \n393: ---\n394: \n395: ## Testing Strategy\n396: \n397: ### 6.1 Unit Test Matrix\n398: \n399: #### PublishRuntime Tests (`tests/runtime/test_publish_runtime.py`)\n400: \n401: | Test Name | Description |\n402: |-----------|-------------|\n403: | `TestPublishRuntime_ValidAgentCubePublish` | Valid workspace, agentcube provider → publishes CR successfully |\n404: | `TestPublishRuntime_ValidK8sPublish` | Valid workspace, k8s provider → publishes Deployment + Service |\n405: | `TestPublishRuntime_MissingWorkspace` | Non-existent path → `ValueError` |\n406: | `TestPublishRuntime_MissingImageUrlLocal` | Local build mode, no image_url → `ValueError` |\n407: | `TestPublishRuntime_MissingRouterUrl` | AgentCube provider, no router_url → `ValueError` |\n408: | `TestPublishRuntime_MissingWorkloadManagerUrl` | AgentCube provider, no workload_manager_url → `ValueError` |\n409: | `TestPublishRuntime_InvalidNodePort` | node_port=9999 → `ValueError` |\n410: | `TestPublishRuntime_DockerUnavailable` | Local mode, Docker down → `RuntimeError` |\n411: | `TestPublishRuntime_CloudImageResolution` | Cloud mode, image URL from metadata → resolves correctly |\n412: | `TestPublishRuntime_MetadataUpdate` | Metadata updated with deployment info after publish |\n413: | `TestPublishRuntime_VersionOverride` | `--version` overrides metadata version |\n414: | `TestPublishRuntime_DeploymentTimeout` | K8s deployment not ready → `RuntimeError` |\n415: | `TestPublishRuntime_UnsupportedProvider` | provider=\"unknown\" → `ValueError` |\n416: | `TestPublishRuntime_UnsupportedBuildMode` | build_mode=\"unknown\" → `ValueError` |\n417: \n418: #### CLI Command Tests (`tests/cli/test_publish_command.py`)\n419: \n420: | Test Name | Description |\n421: |-----------|-------------|\n422: | `TestPublishCommand_SuccessAgentCube` | `publish --provider agentcube` → success output, exit 0 |\n423: | `TestPublishCommand_SuccessK8s` | `publish --provider k8s` → success output, exit 0 |\n424: | `TestPublishCommand_Defaults` | `publish` (no options) → uses defaults |\n425: | `TestPublishCommand_VerboseError` | Exception + `--verbose` → red error + traceback, exit 1 |\n426: | `TestPublishCommand_QuietError` | Exception, no `--verbose` → red error only, exit 1 |\n427: | `TestPublishCommand_ProgressSpinner` | Runs with Rich Progress spinner visible |\n428: \n429: #### AgentCubeProvider Tests (`tests/services/test_agentcube_provider.py`)\n430: \n431: | Test Name | Description |\n432: |-----------|-------------|\n433: | `TestAgentCubeProvider_DeployCR` | Creates AgentRuntime CR with correct spec |\n434: | `TestAgentCubeProvider_EnvVarFallback` | Missing env vars fall back to os.environ |\n435: | `TestAgentCubeProvider_SessionConfig` | CR has sessionTimeout=15m, maxSessionDuration=8h |\n436: | `TestAgentCubeProvider_ImagePullSecrets` | CR has imagePullSecrets=[{\"name\": \"default-secret\"}] |\n437: | `TestAgentCubeProvider_SanitizeName` | Invalid chars replaced, truncated to 63 chars |\n438: | `TestAgentCubeProvider_GetAgentRuntime` | Retrieves existing CR by name |\n439: \n440: #### KubernetesProvider Tests (`tests/services/test_k8s_provider.py`)\n441: \n442: | Test Name | Description |\n443: |-----------|-------------|\n444: | `TestK8sProvider_DeployAgent` | Creates Deployment + NodePort Service |\n445: | `TestK8sProvider_WaitForReady` | Waits until deployment ready, returns |\n446: | `TestK8sProvider_WaitTimeout` | Timeout exceeded → `TimeoutError` |\n447: | `TestK8sProvider_NodePortRange` | NodePort in 30000-32767 range |\n448: | `TestK8sProvider_ServiceUrl` | Service URL format: `http://localhost:{node_port}` |\n449: | `TestK8sProvider_DeleteAgent` | Deletes Deployment + Service, ignores 404 |\n450: \n451: ### 6.2 Test Helpers\n452: \n453: ```python\n454: @pytest.fixture\n455: def workspace_with_metadata(tmp_path: Path) -> Path:\n456:     ws = tmp_path / \"my-agent\"\n457:     ws.mkdir()\n458:     (ws / \"main.py\").write_text(\"print('hello')\\n\")\n459:     (ws / \"agent_metadata.yaml\").write_text(\n460:         \"agent_name: test-agent\\n\"\n461:         \"language: python\\n\"\n462:         \"entrypoint: python main.py\\n\"\n463:         \"port: 8080\\n\"\n464:         \"build_mode: local\\n\"\n465:         \"router_url: http://router.example.com\\n\"\n466:         \"workload_manager_url: http://wm.example.com\\n\"\n467:     )\n468:     return ws\n469: \n470: @pytest.fixture\n471: def mock_docker_service(mocker):\n472:     service = mocker.patch(\"agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime.DockerService\")\n473:     service.return_value.check_docker_available.return_value = True\n474:     service.return_value.push_image.return_value = {\"pushed_image\": \"registry.example.com/my-agent:v1.0.0\"}\n475:     return service\n476: \n477: @pytest.fixture\n478: def mock_agentcube_provider(mocker):\n479:     provider = mocker.patch(\"agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime.AgentCubeProvider\")\n480:     provider.return_value.deploy_agent_runtime.return_value = {\n481:         \"name\": \"test-agent\",\n482:         \"endpoint\": \"http://router.example.com/v1/...\",\n483:     }\n484:     return provider\n485: \n486: @pytest.fixture\n487: def mock_k8s_provider(mocker):\n488:     provider = mocker.patch(\"agentcube.runtime.publish_runtime.KubernetesProvider\")\n489:     provider.return_value.deploy_agent.return_value = {\n490:         \"deployment_name\": \"test-agent\",\n491:         \"service_name\": \"test-agent\",\n492:         \"service_url\": \"http://localhost:30080\",\n493:         \"node_port\": 30080,\n494:     }\n495:     return provider\n496: ```\n497: \n498: ### 6.3 Mock Strategy\n499: \n500: - **Filesystem:** Use `pytest` `tmp_path` fixture for isolated workspaces\n501: - **MetadataService:** Real instance (lightweight, no external deps)\n502: - **DockerService:** Mock `check_docker_available`, `push_image`, `_docker_login_sdk`\n503: - **AgentCubeProvider:** Mock `deploy_agent_runtime`, `get_agent_runtime`\n504: - **KubernetesProvider:** Mock `deploy_agent`, `wait_for_deployment_ready`, `get_agent_status`\n505: - **Console output:** Capture via `capfd` or `rich.console.Console(record=True)`\n506: \n507: ### 6.4 Gate Requirements\n508: \n509: 1. `pytest tests/ -v` all pass\n510: 2. `pytest tests/ --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing` coverage ≥ 80%\n511: 3. `ruff check agentcube/` no violations\n512: 4. `mypy agentcube/` no type errors\n513: 5. All PublishRuntime public methods have unit tests\n514: 6. Error paths tested (invalid workspace, missing URLs, bad node_port, timeout)\n515: 7. Both provider flows tested (agentcube and k8s)\n516: \n517: ---\n518: \n519: ## Implementation Notes\n520: \n521: 1. **Image preparation is provider-agnostic** — the same image URL is used regardless of target provider\n522: 2. **Metadata is the source of truth** — CLI options override metadata, but metadata is updated with final deployment state\n523: 3. **Namespace resolution order:** CLI option → metadata → default (\"default\")\n524: 4. **Version handling:** If `--version` provided, update metadata; otherwise use existing metadata version or \"latest\"\n525: 5. **Credential security:** Image credentials passed via CLI options are not logged even in verbose mode\n526: 6. **Concurrent deployments:** No locking mechanism; concurrent publishes to same namespace may cause conflicts\n527: 7. **CR status polling:** AgentCube provider polls CR status field for readiness; K8s provider uses `wait_for_deployment_ready` with 120s timeout\n528: 8. **NodePort validation:** Validated at CLI level (30000-32767) before reaching provider\n529: 9. **Environment variable fallback:** AgentCube provider falls back to `os.environ.get(\"WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL\")` and `os.environ.get(\"ROUTER_URL\")` if not in metadata\n\n(End of file - total 529 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-022 — CLI publish 命令 — Design\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `publish` command deploys a packaged and built agent to a target Kubernetes cluster. It supports two providers:\n- **`agentcube`** (default): Deploys an AgentRuntime Custom Resource (CR) to `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n- **`k8s`**: Deploys standard Kubernetes Deployment + NodePort Service\n\nThe command handles image preparation (local Docker push or cloud image URL), provider-specific deployment, metadata updates, and readiness verification. It is the third step in the agent lifecycle pipeline: `pack → build → publish → invoke`.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### 2.1 Data Flow\n\n```\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                          CLI (Typer)                                  │\n│   kubectl-agentcube publish -f <workspace> [--provider agentcube]    │\n└────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                         │ options dict","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-022/design.md","time":{"start":1775854352592,"end":1775854352599}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775854353877,"sessionID":"ses_286d7bf5effezn8f6G9VP0lIdu","part":{"id":"prt_d792af961001M9spJo9NeIcR8O","messageID":"msg_d792ae369001LYI7xn1mjDWpxz","sessionID":"ses_286d7bf5effezn8f6G9VP0lIdu","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_a12fb35a96f0490ca40ea562","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Docker service for checking daemon availability and building images.\"\"\"\n2: \n3: from __future__ import annotations\n4: \n5: import time\n6: from pathlib import Path\n7: from typing import Dict, Optional\n8: \n9: import docker\n10: \n11: \n12: class DockerService:\n13:     \"\"\"Service for interacting with the local Docker daemon.\"\"\"\n14: \n15:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n16:         self.verbose = verbose\n17: \n18:     def check_docker_available(self) -> bool:\n19:         \"\"\"Check if the Docker daemon is running and reachable.\"\"\"\n20:         try:\n21:             client = docker.from_env()\n22:             client.ping()\n23:             return True\n24:         except Exception:\n25:             return False\n26: \n27:     def build_image(\n28:         self,\n29:         dockerfile_path: Path,\n30:         context_path: Path,\n31:         image_name: str,\n32:         tag: str = \"latest\",\n33:         build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n34:     ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n35:         \"\"\"Build a Docker image and return metadata about the result.\"\"\"\n36:         client = docker.from_env()\n37:         start_time = time.time()\n38: \n39:         image, logs = client.images.build(\n40:             path=str(context_path),\n41:             dockerfile=str(dockerfile_path),\n42:             tag=f\"{image_name}:{tag}\",\n43:             buildargs=build_args,\n44:         )\n45: \n46:         build_time = time.time() - start_time\n47:         image_info = client.images.get(image.id)\n48: \n49:         return {\n50:             \"image_name\": image_name,\n51:             \"image_id\": image.short_id,\n52:             \"image_size\": self._format_size(int(image_info.attrs.get(\"Size\", 0) or 0)),\n53:             \"build_time\": f\"{build_time:.2f}s\",\n54:         }\n55: \n56:     def _format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str:\n57:         \"\"\"Format byte count into a human-readable string.\"\"\"\n58:         if size_bytes < 1024:\n59:             return f\"{size_bytes} B\"\n60:         elif size_bytes < 1024 * 1024:\n61:             return f\"{size_bytes / 1024:.1f} KB\"\n62:         elif size_bytes < 1024 * 1024 * 1024:\n63:             return f\"{size_bytes / (1024 * 1024):.1f} MB\"\n64:         else:\n65:             return f\"{size_bytes / (1024 * 1024 * 1024):.1f} GB\"\n\n(End of file - total 65 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Docker service for checking daemon availability and building images.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport time\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Dict, Optional\n\nimport docker\n\n\nclass DockerService:\n    \"\"\"Service for interacting with the local Docker daemon.\"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None:\n        self.verbose = verbose\n\n    def check_docker_available(self) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Check if the Docker daemon is running and reachable.\"\"\"\n        try:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py","time":{"start":1775854353870,"end":1775854353876}}}}
